H0.text: In humans, Duane Syndrome affects which part of the body. Brain

H1.text: In humans, Duane Syndrome affects which part of the body. Ear

H2.text: In humans, Duane Syndrome affects which part of the body. Nose

H3.text: In humans, Duane Syndrome affects which part of the body. Eye

A4.text: Duane syndrome is a congenital rare type of strabismus most commonly characterized by the inability of the eye to move outward.

A5.text: Duane syndrome is most probably a miswiring of the eye muscles, causing some eye muscles to contract when they shouldn't and other eye muscles not to contract when they should.
